{
  "stem": "304.1",
  "chunk_idx": 14,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We're just-- we're glad we can live and-- with [? our ?]-- [? our ?]-- [? our ?] quiet.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "In 1941, a lot of people from our town, and also around [NON-ENGLISH] that used to be Czechoslovakia, all the Jewish families who didn't have a Czech, originally, or a Hungarian citizenship, they were expelled from the country.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And they were taken to Poland.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And we didn't know about them anything.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But one family, who lived across the street from us, they came back, the whole family, parents and three children.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "The youngest daughter was my friend.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "She lives here in Los Angeles, and we talk about it sometimes.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And they came back.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And they told us the stories, how the Germans tell the Jewish people to dig their own graves.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And they shoved them in.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "But it was so horrible that we didn't believe it.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "We didn't want to believe it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And I-- it was so-- I think it's human nature that we didn't want to believe it.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And we-- mainly, we hoped it will not happen to us.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And even though some people listened carefully and they tried to go away, it wasn't easy to leave the place and go away.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Because the tragedy, the second part of the tragedy, was that nobody opened the gates for us to say, OK you are in danger in Hungary, or Germany, or Poland, come to us.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "So it wasn't easy.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "So we had to sit and wait and hope and pray.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "No way.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Maybe to Romania, or-- or-- or-- it was very hard, because in the minute the Hungarians came in, the borders were closed.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So to go somewhere, you had to really go on-- hiding.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
